## Proposed Changes

---

### Phase 1 — Fix PSSS Bug (Prerequisite, ~1 session)

#### [MODIFY] [secret_sharing.py](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py)
- Add `Union` to typing imports (fixes lint + runtime `NameError`)
- Fix [reconstruct_packed_secret](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py#229-326): polynomial ops ([poly_mul](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py#256-263), [poly_add](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py#264-272), [poly_scalar_mul](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py#273-275)) currently call `int()` on values that may be numpy arrays — this causes the `ValueError: truth value of array is ambiguous`
- Fix: remove forced `int()` casts; instead use Python-native arithmetic that works with both scalars and arrays; handle the `isinstance(yj, np.ndarray)` case explicitly

#### [MODIFY] [client.py](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/client.py)
- Default `packing_l = 1` (backward compat with standard SSS)
- When `packing_l > 1`, use PSSS block packing

#### [MODIFY] [secure_aggregator.py](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secure_aggregator.py)
- Pass `l` to [SecretSharingBuffer](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secret_sharing.py#384-641) from client's `packing_l`
- Fix [_to_tensor_dict](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/secure_aggregator.py#259-294) to reshape flat numpy arrays back to original tensor shape

