### Phase 3 — Novel Analyses (~2 sessions)

#### [NEW] [threshold_analysis.py](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/threshold_analysis.py)
**Our key differentiating contribution** — no other paper does a systematic threshold sweep.

Generates 3 publication-quality figures:
1. **Threshold vs. Final Accuracy** — line plot, one curve per attack type (no attack, 10%, 20%, 30% malicious)
2. **Threshold vs. Convergence Speed** — rounds needed to reach 80% accuracy across `t` values  
3. **Security-Accuracy Tradeoff Heatmap** — 2D grid: x=threshold, y=mal_fraction, z=accuracy (color). Shows the "safe operating region" of PSSS.

```bash
python threshold_analysis.py --experiment mnist --cfg_file_path data/mnist_10/cfg.json \
  --threshold_values "2,3,4,5,6,7,8" --mal_fractions "0.0,0.1,0.2,0.3" --n_rounds 20
```

#### [NEW] [psss_efficiency.py](file:///Users/amaansiddiqui/Desktop/Our-Fed/psss_efficiency.py)
Empirical validation of PSSS communication savings:

- Vary `l ∈ {1, 5, 10, 20, 50}` on MNIST/CIFAR-10/CIFAR-100
- Measure: bytes per round, wall-clock time per round, final accuracy
- Plot: 3-panel figure showing all three metrics vs `l`
- Creates the "model agnostic" proof: same `l` works across CNN, ResNet-9, ResNet-18

